description: Arcane's rival, Carla Jeffries takes over his business. Swamp Thing discovers that she's a much more formidable enemy than Arcane ever was. Will he, Arcane and Graham put their differences aside to oust Carla?
name: Lesser of Two Evils

description: Graham leads a team of heavily armed mercenaries into the swamp to kill Swamp Thing once and for all. Can Tressa save him?
name: Revelations

description: A hunter and his tree-hugging environmentalist son search the swamp for an endangered hawk. Their conflict may prove deadly for Will who inexplicably obtains part of Swamp Thing’s power over nature to try to help the hunted hawk.
name: Easy Prey

description: Arcane hosts a science conference, but it's crashed by an ex-employee of his; a professional hit man who used to work for Sunderland and now has a score to settle. Swamp Thing discovers that the hit man is the same hit man responsible for Alec's transformation and the death of Alec's wife.
name: "The Handyman

description: A chemical plant causing toxic damage to the swamp is the key to a darker future for Swamp Thing.
name: Future Tense

description: When Dr. Arcane "dies" during a mutation experiment gone wrong, Graham accuses Stella of attempting to replace him in the lab by seducing Arcane. During their fight Graham falls for Stella, conceding that Arcane must have seduced her "in mind, if not body." Their tender moment is ruined, however, when Graham is alerted to a break-in at the lab: it's Dr. Arcane, reduced to his inner beast by the failed experiment. Can Graham stop him before tragedy strikes?
name: Hide in the Night

description: Three convicts escape from prison in search of loot from a Las Vegas heist buried in the swamp. One by one they learn the justice of the swamp thanks to Swamp Thing.
name: Pay Day

description: Arcane is convinced that Carter LaRoche is attacking him in the night. But LaRoche is locked up in an insane asylum. And he's getting pretty friendly with Will.
name: The Return of LaRoche

description: Will leads two spoiled girls on a journey through the swamp that tests their character.
name: Rites of Passage

description: A lunatic escapes from a local asylum and knocks on Tressa's door late at night. He proclaims himself as an alien killer. Even Swamp Thing is in danger.
name: Never Alone

description: Arcane, trapped in a cave with an unconscious Swamp Thing, launches into a monologue that sheds light on his motivations and (deep, enormous) neuroses.
name: A Most Bitter Pill

description: Arcane and a scheming hack journalist unearth a cursed mummy.
name: The Curse

description: Will's arrested for a murder he didn't commit.
name: Judgment Day

description: Tressa’s long estranged sister returns looking for shelter from an enemy of her husband and ends up putting the swamp in danger.
name: Eye of the Storm

description: Arcane wines and dines a pretty reporter. But she's not who she claims to be.
name: Vendetta

description: When an elderly woman, named Irma Swanson, who knew and befriended Swamp Thing, dies, her estranged daughter, Cathy, comes to town for her funeral. Swamp Thing and the spirit of Irma then show Cathy the past of Irma’s troubled life in order for Cathy to make amends meet.
name: The Hurting

description: Will falls in love with a woman who claims to have known him in a past life.
name: The Burning Times

description: Arcane and Graham are haunted by a poltergeist. A familiar one.
name: The Specter of Death

description: An experiment gone awry turns Arcane into a kind-hearted good guy and renders Swamp Thing evil and insane.
name: Cross-Fired

description: An old man has a deadly, infectious virus that only Alec's blood can cure. Arcane tries to exploit the disease for himself.
name: Patient Zero

description: A mysterious couple search the swamp for the legendary Fountain of Youth. Unfortunately the megalomaniac Arcane learns about the couple’s plans and tries to find the fountain first, as Will is caught in the middle of the couple’s debate of whether the fountain exists.
name: The Chains of Forever

description: Arcane accidentally creates a half-plant/half-robot. Can Swamp Thing and Will stop this madness?
name: In the Beginning

description: A man is dating Tressa but after a strange phone call, he runs away from her.
name: Brotherly Love

description: A magical cougar from the swamp stalks Arcane determined to kill him and all his associates for the construction of a waste producing nuclear reactor and with Swamp Thing incapable of helping, it’s up to Will to try to rescue the evil doctor before the cougar kills him and spreads its evil to others.
name: An Eye for an Eye

description: A little boy dreams of being a pirate, so Swamp Thing gives him his wish.
name: Yo Ho Ho

description: The gods make a bet and the swamp is the playground.
name: Heart of Stone

description: Arcane falls in love with a model. But will his counterfeit emeralds scheme doom their romance?
name: Romancing Arcane

description: Swamp Thing gets addicted to hallucinogenic iguana eggs which makes him live out a fantasy with Ann. But the effect causes bad luck with Will when he comes into contact with one of them and ends up a prisoner in Arcane’s lab who is determined to find the nest of rare eggs himself for personal use.
name: Swamp of Dreams

description: One of Arcane's mentors, Oliver Duncan, has died, taking his secret research into Cold Fusion with him. Arcane's determined to get at what's left of his research by seducing Oliver's daughter, Louise. But Louise has plans of her own.
name: Heart of the Mantis

description: Jimmy, Clark Kent and Lana Lang's friend, is ashamed that his father works as a doorman at the Smallville theater. His opinion changes when Superboy is able to thwart a robbery with Jimmy's father's help.
name: Pilot

description: An alien ship uses an energy creature to attack Earth
name: The Force Phantom

description: Scuba divers are captured for sport by malevolent fish beings led by Triton.
name: The Mermen of Emor

description: Two giant flying monsters are freed from frozen suspension
name: The Prehistoric Pterodactyls

description: Lex Luthor uses a temporal communicator to discover magic powers
name: Merlin's Magic Marbles

description: An alien space probe trapped in Earth orbit uses force to try to return to its home galaxy.
name: The Threat of the Thrutans

description: A male witch called the Warlock must seize a rare gem that contains powerful magic
name: The Wicked Warlock

description: "The Chimp Who Made It Big" - The fusion of two irradiated pieces of space debris fatefully changes a chimpanzee named Toto on board a space craft. When the capsule containing the space craft lands on Earth, the chimpanzee ends up turning into Titano . Despite Titano causing destruction (and grabbing Lois), Superman must convince the military not to open fire as he thinks he can revert Titano to Toto. *
name: The Chimp Who Made It Big

description: Saboteurs have rigged gigantic icebergs with explosives to rob a luxury liner.
name: The Deadly Icebergs

description: Lois and Jimmy are kidnapped by alien hunters whose "zoo" is protected by a giant robot
name: The Robot of Riga

description: The Sorcerer, a malevolent wizard, uses hirelings using an invisibility field to commit crimes.
name: The Invisible Raiders

description: Jimmy falls into an underground pocket populated by malevolent creatures.
name: The Neolithic Nightmare

description: An alien computer named Brainiac has been capturing different kinds of animals by shrinking them. Brainiac is taking the tiny animals to his dying homeworld on his spaceship. When he also must find a man and woman for repopulation, Brainiac ends up shrinking and capturing Superman and Lois.
name: The Return of Brainiac

description: A magnetic device that melts metal objects is used by alien beings on Earth.
name: The Magnetic Monster

description: Phoning in an anonymous tip to lure Lois Lane and Jimmy Olsen to an abandoned factory on the outskirts of Metropolis, the Toyman captures Lois and Jimmy to help launch a wave of crime and keep Superman away.
name: The Toys of Doom

description: A shape-shifting alien creature that emerged from a fallen meteorite who devours metal structures raises havoc.
name: The Iron Eater

description: In South America, an exiled military officer named Colonel Vasta and a disgraced scientist named Dr. Rucas control apes, with the transmitter on Dr. Rucas's back, in a plot to rob an underground treasure. Lois is caught, tied to a pillar and gagged, and Rucas activates an Inca Statue to crush her.
name: The Ape Army of the Amazon

description: A living flame from Earth's core appears and sets off a mammoth forest fire.
name: The Fire Phantom

description: Lex Luthor traps Lois, Jimmy, and Perry so he can lure Superman into range of a Kryptonite transmitter. *
name: The Deadly Dish

description: Criminals who have perfected insect powers must stop Superman from foiling their wave of crime.
name: The Insect Raiders

description: The Warlock steals a magic gem to wreak havoc on Superman's friends.
name: Return of Warlock

description: An ice being freezes tropical Hawaii where Lois Lane is having her vacation. *
name: The Abominable Iceman

description: "The Men from A.P.E." - Lex Luthor, The Warlock, Toyman and Prankster form the organization A.P.E. (Allied Perpetrators of Evil) and combine their powers to defeat Superman.
name: The Men from A.P.E.

description: A tree being brought to life near a meteor crater consumes enormous quantities of water.
name: The Tree Man of Arbora

description: A mid-ocean earthquake releases a giant lobster and a giant alligator.
name: Superman's Double Truble

description: A master criminal scientist named Luna (AKA Professor Leo Nula) captures Lois in order to send her into space within his 4D movie as part of his revenge on her for sending him to prison seven years ago.
name: The Image Maker

description: The Sorcerer uses a voodoo doll to stop Superman.
name: The Deadly Super-Doll

description: In Mexico, a volcano creates living beings of lava.
name: Lava Men

description: Lex Luthor uses Jimmy Olsen as bait to use Kryptonite laser beam weapons against Superman in a paint factory.
name: Luthor Strikes Again

description: Alien raiders forced to Earth recruit Superman to rescue hostages on their home world.
name: Mission to Planet Peril

description: While breaking into a science lab, a petty criminal named I. C. Harris is exposed to a radioactive isotope and achieves power to drain physical strength from other men. With his new power, he aims to become a "Superman of Crime." But when he discovers the real Superman, Harris's unstoppable greed for physical power proves fatal.
name: The Pernicious Parasite

description: The Toyman creates a robot of The Man Of Steel.
name: The Two Faces of Superman

description: A carnival is raided by an extra-dimensional prankster known as Mister Mxyzptlk
name: The Imp-Practical Joker

description: Brainiac raids Earth to gather creatures to repopulate a planet devastated by atomic wars.
name: Superman Meets Brainiac

description: Alien seed pods grow plants that destroy other objects.
name: Seeds of Disaster

description: An Egyptian sorcerer in mummified form attacks Lois and Superman.
name: The Malevolent Mummy

description: Avian beings must raid outside farmlands for survival because a gold raider named Trask and his henchmen hold their populace hostage.
name: The Birdmen from Lost Valley

description: Lex Luthor, Brainiac and Warlock come together as A.P.E. in a plot to steal a crime-detecting computer.
name: A.P.E. Strikes Again

description: A lighting storm irradiates a lightning bug to create a gigantic energy creature.
name: The Lethal Lightning Bug

description: "A petty nuisance called the Prankster creates havoc until Superman uses tricks of his own.
name: The Prankster

description: Lois and Clark are captured on a freighter by criminals dumping radioactive waste into Metropolis Harbor.
name: The Saboteurs

description: The spiritual essence of an alien warlord snares innocent men on Earth.
name: The Wisp of Wickedness

description: A Kryptonite meteor crashes into the ocean and releases a giant creature with the same powers as Superman.
name: Superman Meets His Match

description: An unmanned alien probe that resembles a metal octopus attacks Earth near the Niagara Falls.
name: Night of the Octopod

description: Following a traumatic attack on City Hall, flashbacks show how Rene became Wild Dog.
name: Spectre of the Gun

description:
David Haller entered a whole new world. He was rescued by Sydney, with the help of mutants Ptonomy and Kerry and their leader, psychiatrist Melanie Bird. This episode, aptly titled “Chapter 2,” will follow David as he leaves whatever government facility he was being held in and enters the outside world.

However large this world turns out to be, it will represent a huge change of pace for David. He had been a resident of the Clockworks Mental Hospital for six years and become accustomed to its pace and it’s environment and somewhat dependent on the drugs provided.
name: Chapter 2

description: Criminals force a scientist who has created a growth ray for honeybees to use the device to attack Metropolis.
name: War of the Bee Battalion

description: The Toyman and his henchman use a gigantic insect robot fitted with a Kryptonite beam weapon against Superman at a nuclear facility.
name: The Toyman's Super-Toy

description: Brainiac shrinks Metropolis itself to minuscule size and imprisons the city in glass for return to Doctor Heckla's homeworld
name: The Cage of Glass

description: When Superman innocently tests a powerful liquid fuel by drinking it at the request of a scientist friend, the liquid creates an atomic fire raging inside his body that makes him blast out fire whenever he opens his mouth, forcing him to exile.
name: The Atomic Superman

description: Lex Luthor invents a mirror that can transport people to his hideout at an abandoned amusement park and with such traps Jimmy Olsen.
name: Luthor's Loco Looking Glass

description: The Warlock's sister frees him from prison and he launches an all-out campaign against Lois Lane.
name: The Warlock's Revenge

description: A giant ice creature in Asia assaults the mountainous regions of India and Pakistan.
name: The Halyah of the Himalayas

description: Lex Luthor captures Jimmy Olsen to lure Superman to the West Coast where he unleashes a bombardment of fireworks laced with Kryptonite.
name: Luthor's Fatal Fireworks

description: Jimmy Olsen and Lois Lane discover a spacecraft in a nearby canyon, but are captured by Lex Luthor , who flies to the moon to set up a giant laser cannon to attack Earth.
name: Luthor's Lethal Laser Pt. 1

description: "When Superman rescues Lois and Jimmy, Lex Luthor escapes and teams up with Brainiac to set a trap.
name: Luthor's Lethal Laser  Pt. 2

description: To the disbelief of Jimmy Olsen, Lex Luthor has convinced Perry White that he has gone straight, and has thus become The Daily Planet's science editor with a huge experimental lab in the Planet building. Jimmy's disbelief leads him to try and catch Luthor in a deception, but his efforts lead to disasters.
name: Can a Luthor Change His Spots? Pt. 1

description: Thinking he catches Lex Luthor in a bank robbery, Jimmy Olsen jumps Luthor and closes a bank vault, trapping Perry White and the Metropolis Police Chief, before a bigger disaster strikes the Planet building itself.
name: Can a Luthor Change His Spots? Pt. 2

description: The exiled Queen Satana from the planet Quanta flies to Earth to drain nuclear energy for use in plastic objects called Plasto whose molecular structure can be telepathically altered.
name: The Team of Terror Pt. 1

description: To shake off Superman after he thwarts her efforts, Queen Satana teams with the Warlock to destroy Superman while she unleashes nuclear warfare on Quanta.
name: The Team of Terror Pt. 2

description: Ostensibly on vacation, Lois Lane follows an associate of a fugitive scientist to the southwestern Pacific, while Metropolis is suddenly attacked by giant balls of solid iron plummeting from space.
name: Rain of Iron Pt. 1

description: The fugitive scientist has created a gigantic cannon to launch iron spheres onto Metropolis and has taken island natives hostage to thwart Superman.
name: Rain of Iron Pt. 2

description: none
name: The Japanese Sandman" Pt. 2

description: A being made of mist-like substance emerges from an old water well on Perry White's farm, and can transform into a perfect duplicate of any human by absorbing into a person's abandoned clothing. He binds and gags Lois Lane, planning to take her through a well to the Underworld.
name: "The Mysterious Mr. Mist" Pt. 1

description: The mist being repeatedly attempts to kidnap Lois Lane to make her the queen of his underground society. He put her in a sack and again ties her up at the top of a building, but Superman uses a vacuum to catch him, then saves Lois from falling.
name: The Mysterious Mr. Mist Pt. 2

description: Lex Luthor has created a laser beam transmitter with which he transports two fire beings from a distant star to help him defeat Superman.
name: Luminians on the Loose Part 1

description: When the fire beings turn on him, Lex Luthor must team with Superman to stop them. Meanwhile, the Lumiaians use Lex's transmitter to get a battalion of Luminians to invade Earth.
name: Luminians on the Loose Pt. 2

description: In Scotland, Lois and Jimmy run afoul of two twin brothers whose ancestors stole the castle in which they live, and the ghost of the castle's original ruler has emerged for revenge.
name: The Ghost of Kilbane Castle - Part 1

description: Superman teams with the Kilbane ghost to defeat the two evil twins. They have Lois and Jimmy tied up and gagged above spikes on a tower wall, and threaten to cut them lose if Superman tries to stop them.
name: The Ghost of Kilbane Castle Part 2

description: In Yokohama, a shipping magnate's businesses are sabotaged by an explosives factory owner and the man summons a Japanese god to help him defeat the magnate.
name: The Japanese Sandman  Pt. 1
